title: NFS unrescue fails with: 'Cannot access storage file '/var/lib/nova/mnt/5fd17b88c08c2759966c40234dfd10c0/volume-67bbce20-b476-466d-b20a-8337957af780' (as uid:107, gid:107): No such file or directory'

comments.author: https://api.launchpad.net/1.0/~amortiz

comments.content:
The relevant error is this:

Cannot access storage file '/var/lib/nova/mnt/5fd17b88c08c2759966c40234dfd10c0/volume-67bbce20-b476-466d-b20a-8337957af780' (as uid:107, gid:107): No such file or directory", u'code': 500

Note that this is with an NFS backend.
comments.author: https://api.launchpad.net/1.0/~mriedem

comments.content:
Looks like the unrescue operation failed:

2016-09-23 19:39:46,928 18008 INFO     [tempest.common.waiters] State transition "RESCUE/unrescuing" ==> "ERROR/None" after 1 second wait
comments.author: https://api.launchpad.net/1.0/~mriedem

comments.content:
And then because unrescue failed, the instance was put in ERROR state and the detach_volume after that failed:

Body: {"conflictingRequest": {"message": "Cannot 'detach_volume' instance 04e4aa2a-13ed-44ca-a275-bbb703c12493 while it is in vm_state error", "code": 409}}
comments.author: https://api.launchpad.net/1.0/~mriedem

comments.content:
Oh right, yeah the unrescue failed because of this:

"fault": {"message": "Cannot access storage file '/var/lib/nova/mnt/5fd17b88c08c2759966c40234dfd10c0/volume-67bbce20-b476-466d-b20a-8337957af780' (as uid:107, gid:107): No such file or directory"
comments.author: https://api.launchpad.net/1.0/~mriedem

comments.content:
Is this a duplicate of https://bugs.launchpad.net/nova/+bug/1421550 ?

The associated fix for that bug https://review.openstack.org/#/c/383859/ is almost merged so I'd be interested to see if that resolves this anyway.
